# Legal / Third‑party intake (Wist / Fluffy Flash)

Whenever you add, update, bundle, or copy **any** third‑party component (code, binaries/CLI tools, assets, fonts, scripts, SDKs, data files), you MUST do the following in the same change set:

## 1) Inventory & documentation

- Update `FluffyFlash/THIRD_PARTY.md`:
  - component name + upstream URL
  - license (SPDX if possible)
  - what we use it for
  - whether it ships inside `.app` (runtime redistributed) or is build-time only
  - compliance obligations (e.g., attribution, NOTICE propagation, source offer)

- Update `ObsidianVault/10-Project-Wist/Legal.md`:
  - add/adjust the inventory entry
  - update “release checklist” if obligations changed
  - add risks/notes if license is copyleft/contested/unclear

## 2) Release artifacts (if redistributed)

If the third‑party component is redistributed in the `.app` or in release packages:

- Ensure `FluffyFlash/THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.txt` includes it
- Ensure `FluffyFlash/Scripts/build_third_party_sources_bundle.sh` can produce:
  - `ReleaseArtifacts/third-party/manifest.json`
  - `ReleaseArtifacts/third-party/third-party-sources.tar.gz`

## 3) Safety rails

- Prefer permissive licenses (MIT/BSD/Apache) when possible.
- Treat GPL/LGPL/CDDL/AGPL as “needs explicit plan”:
  - define whether it is a separate program (process boundary) vs linked library
  - define how we will ship corresponding source
  - define where notices live in the distribution

